cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting engagement during human-robot interaction and improving the dialogue strategy of the robot. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper involves using a robot (ERICA) and a Kinect sensor for data collection. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the Kinect sensor is used for capturing visual data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper involves analyzing verbal backchannels in human-robot interaction. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper involves using a microphone array for audio data collection.
